import random

def generate_data():
    target_material = ['aluminium', 'gold', 'plastic'] # Add more materials if needed
    target_thickness = np.random.uniform(low=0, high=150, size=(1,)).flatten()

    energy = np.random.uniform(low=np.percentile(stats['Energy']['data'], 25), high=np.percentile(stats['Energy']['data'], 75), size=(1,)).flatten()
    spot_size = np.random.normal(loc=np.mean(stats['Spot Size']['data']), scale=np.std(stats['Spot Size']['data']), size=(1,)).flatten()
    intensity = 10**(np.random.uniform(low=-3, high=5, size=(1,)).flatten()) # Adjust the range to fit your data distribution
    power = np.random.uniform(low=np.percentile(stats['Power']['data'], 25), high=np.percentile(stats['Power']['data'], 75), size=(1,)).flatten() * 1e12 # Adjust scale to fit your data distribution
